[1]	Here, perhaps Paul was ready to end his letter to the Philippians.
However, he continues to rewrite some of the things that he has commanded to them before.

[2]	Look out for:
The dogs: The Judiaisers who believed that the Mosaic law must be followed in addition to faith in Jesus Christ.
Paul calls them the false circumcision.

[3]	"Real circumcision" in contrast to the Judiaisers who are the false circumcision.

[4-6]	Confidence -> from Latin: Confidae.
Since the Judiaisers have confidence in the works of the flesh, but Paul has achieved every confidence of the flesh -- and he counts it as worthless.

